# =============================================================================
# QUIET AND JSON MODE BEHAVIOR
# =============================================================================
#
# --quiet / -q :
#   Suppresses ALL non-error output (info, success, warnings, help text,
#   status messages, progress, etc.).
#   Only critical errors are printed (as plain text on stderr or as JSON
#   error object when --json is also used).
#
# --json :
#   Enables strict machine-readable JSON output for scripting and automation.
#   Automatically implies --quiet (no human-readable text is ever emitted).
#   The script MUST output EXACTLY ONE valid JSON object per execution and
#   then exit. Never output more than one JSON object, partial JSON, or any
#   other text (including newlines outside the object).
#
#   JSON Output Rules (Strict - Canonical Specification):
#   - Always starts with: {"type": "success|status|error|about|version|...", ...}
#   - "message" field is optional and should only be included when it adds
#     meaningful human-readable context (even in JSON mode).
#   - All numbers (version numbers, counts, ports, etc.) MUST be unquoted.
#   - All strings (paths, domains, email, status, versions) MUST be quoted.
#   - Booleans (true/false) and null are allowed without quotes.
#   - Arrays and objects are fully supported when they add value (e.g. domain list).
#   - Use consistent, predictable field names across all commands (e.g. always
#     "version", "domains", "email", "count", "code", etc.).
#   - Never use duplicate keys.
#   - Output must be valid JSON (no trailing commas, proper escaping).
#   - Prefer compact output (no pretty-printing) unless explicitly needed.
#
#   Supported "type" values (expandable but keep these core ones):
#     success, status, error, about, version, version_check
#
#   All output MUST go through output_text() or output_json() — never use
#   raw echo, printf, or cat outside these functions.
#
#   When both --quiet and --json are used, --json takes absolute precedence.
#
# =============================================================================
# RECOMMENDED JSON EXAMPLES (certbot-nginx specific)
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Success (simple)
#    {"type":"success","message":"Setup completed successfully"}
#
# 2. Success with data
#    {"type":"success","message":"Certificates obtained","main_domain":"git.example.com","domains":["git.example.com","app.example.com"],"count":2}
